    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Here's what a solution looks like:\n\n```\nimport re\nimport subprocess\nr_alias = re.compile(r\"alias .+='.+'\")\nlines = subprocess.check_output('echo alias|bash -i',shell=True).split('\\n')\nmanager = get_ipython().alias_manager\nfor line in lines:\n    if r_alias.match(line):\n        # cut off 'alias' preamble\n        line = ' '.join(line.split()[1:])\n        split_index = line.find('=')\n        cmd = line[split_index+1:]\n        alias = line[:split_index]\n        # cut off the quotes that always surrounded the command\n        cmd = cmd[1:-1]\n        print alias,cmd\n        manager.soft_define_alias(alias, cmd)\n```\n"
  },
