    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Thanks for your report. I'm going through cleaning up old issues, and I think it makes sense to close this one. This issue is quite old now and it is unlikely that we will ever support this in stock IPython, among other reasons one contributing factor is that IPython runs on platforms that do not come with bash at all (Windows, for example), as well as there being a bunch of different shells to choose from and shell preferences among the unix-like operating systems.\n\nIt's worth mentioning here that IPython does support its own `alias` mechanisms (read `%alias?` for more), as well as the execution of bash commands (via `%%bash` cell magic).\n\nHappy hacking! :bowtie:\n"
